# ⚙️ COA Concept 4: Near-Memory Processing

🔥 Advanced memory optimization concept.

---

## 1️⃣ Problem

CPU spends huge time waiting for memory transfers.

---

## Solution

Move computation closer to memory.

---

## Difference from In-Memory Computing

* In-memory → compute inside memory
* Near-memory → compute near memory

---

## Why Useful?

✔ lower latency
✔ reduced bandwidth pressure
✔ energy efficiency

---

## 🧠 Real-World Analogy

Small kitchen near warehouse instead of transporting materials far away.

---

## 🔗 Connection

Solves:

👉 memory bottlenecks

---

## 🎯 Placement Question

**Q: Why near-memory processing improves performance?**

👉 Because it reduces expensive data movement between CPU and memory.

---

## 🧠 Memory Trick

```text id="2p6qra"
Move compute closer to data
```

